verbose_text: Pathogenesis of hyperlipidaemic AP is associated with obstruction of the pancreatic microcirculation by blood lipids, and injury of pancreatic acinar cells by free fatty acids and abnormally activated trypsinogen.
evidence: AP is associated with obstruction of the pancreatic microcirculation by blood lipids, and injury of pancreatic acinar cells by free fatty acids and abnormally activated trypsinogen
